# Styling Guide

This document outlines the styling approach and design system used in the portfolio website.

## CSS Variables

The website uses CSS variables for consistent theming defined in [styles/globals.css](mdc:styles/globals.css). Key variables include:

```css
:root {
  /* Colors */
  --bg-dark: #0F172A;
  --bg-card: #1E293B;
  --bg-card-hover: #293548;
  --text: #E2E8F0;
  --text-light: #94A3B8;
  --text-bright: #F8FAFC;
  --accent: #0EA5E9;
  --accent-hover: #0284C7;
  --secondary-accent: #8B5CF6;
  --border-subtle: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);
  
  /* Gradients */
  --accent-gradient: linear-gradient(90deg, #0EA5E9, #8B5CF6);
  --subtle-gradient: linear-gradient(135deg, #0EA5E9, #8B5CF6);

  /* Spacing */
  --section-spacing: 5rem;
  
  /* Borders */
  --border-radius: 8px;
  --border-radius-sm: 6px;
  --border-radius-lg: 12px;
  
  /* Transitions */
  --transition-normal: all 0.3s ease;
  --transition-fast: all 0.2s ease;
}
```

## Class Naming Conventions

The website follows these naming conventions:

1. Bootstrap classes for layout and spacing (e.g., `container`, `row`, `col`, `mb-4`)
2. Custom component-specific classes:
   - Container elements: `{component-name}-container`
   - Item elements: `{component-name}-item`
   - Sub-elements: `{component-name}-{element-purpose}`

Example:
```html
<div className="tech-skills-container">
  <div className="tech-skills-grid">
    <div className="tech-skill-item">
      <div className="tech-skill-icon">...</div>
      <div className="tech-skill-name">...</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
```

## Responsive Design

The layout uses Bootstrap's responsive grid system with these breakpoints:

- xs: < 576px (Mobile phones)
- sm: ≥ 576px (Small tablets)
- md: ≥ 768px (Tablets)
- lg: ≥ 992px (Desktops)
- xl: ≥ 1200px (Large desktops)

## Animation Styles

Animations use CSS transitions and keyframes:

1. Hover effects with `transform` and `box-shadow`
2. Section reveal with `opacity` and `transform`
3. Special effects with custom `@keyframes`

## Common Element Styles

- Cards: `shadow-sm border-subtle` with hover effects
- Buttons: `btn-primary` or `btn-outline-light` with standard Bootstrap styling
- Icons: Size and color variations based on context


